  "title": "Accountant-Manufacturing",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage full sets of accounts and prepare financial statements in accordance with SFRS / IFRS and group reporting requirements.</li><li>Oversee budgeting, cost control, and financial analysis to support management decisions.</li><li>Handle import and export accounting, including revenue and cost recognition based on trade documents and Incoterms (e.g. FOB, CIF).</li><li>Manage GST matters, including import GST claims, output GST reporting, and GST treatment for cross-border transactions.</li><li>Support corporate income tax planning and liaise with auditors and external parties for statutory filings and annual audits.</li><li>Maintain compliance-related documentation and liaise with banks and financial institutions as required.</li><li>Collaborate closely with cross-border teams in China and Germany to ensure the smooth and efficient operation of the finance system.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Requirements</strong></li></ul><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related fields.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant accounting or finance experience.</li><li>Experience with manufacture company is preferred.</li></ul>",
